<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="2cec1dcf-94de-5284-86b1-28f3547e0d40" activityNameId="5bc4e6f5-356a-464b-81ac-3b74be1bfc31" parentActivityId="97c631d2-5575-44fb-8818-341be0db6c99" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cement production, CEM II/A-L</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CEM II A-L</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Portland Limestone Cement</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From the reception of raw materials at the cement factory.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the CEM II/A-L cement produced in the cement silos (after milling). The dataset does not include packaging and administration.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The information details the manufacturing of CEM II/A-L cement using milled limestone and gypsum as fillers. Tunisia has five types of cement (CEM I to CEM V) based on the supplementary cementitious materials (limestone). In terms of mass composition, CEM II/A-L has 5% to 20% limestone filler. Tunisian standards (NT 47.01 (2017)) specify the five cement types. Tunisian cement output is represented by five different kinds of cement. The table below summarizes the various cement kinds and compositions as defined by Tunisian specifications (NT 47.01).(2017). Clinker, gypsum, and limestone made CEM I cement (see composition in the table). This dataset covers data from the clinker stockpile to the cement suitable for bulk shipment. After cooling from the rotary kiln, the clinker is pulverized in ball mills to particles less than 75 mm in size. It is then transported to silos and combined with calcium sulfate (gypsum) and limestone. The combined cement is transported to a finishing mill and then kept in cement silos until it is delivered in bulk or packaged (kraft paper). Primary data was collected from one cement factory in Tunisia, who informed the total values of cement production inputs and outputs in 2019. Primary and secondary raw materials and fuels, auxiliary materials, energy, and water use were all recorded. It equates to a 15% market share. Particulate emissions may occur. However they are not recorded owing to a lack of data for the cement grinding phase (air emissions are monitored for the integrated clinker-cement plant as a whole and reported in the clinker production process).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The CEM II/A-L manufacturing process consists of four main steps: (1)  Quarrying of limestone and other raw materials to the processing plant. (2) Preparation of “raw meal” for pyroprocessing (3) Pyroprocessing of raw materials to produce clinker using the dry process. (4) Final grinding of the clinker together with inter-grinding with a small proportion of gypsum to produce CEM II/A-L. Steps (1) to (4) are not considered in dataset. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2"></text>
          <imageUrl index="3">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/910a96c9-7e41-4964-9381-bbf6f05378f1</imageUrl>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">NT47.01(2017): Ciment - Partie 1: Composition, spécifications et critères des conformité des ciments courants</text>
          <imageUrl index="5">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/7f22b3b6-049b-42ca-991d-e691d04ace00</imageUrl>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="133fc02a-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">TN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset represents the CEM II/A-L cement production for Tunisia. </text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dry kiln process is used in Tunisia to produce cement. In order to create Portland cement, the clinker is pulverized in mills together with gypsum (3-5%), additional materials like limestone, and/or other ingredients according to national and international standards (Tunisian standard NT 47.01 (2017); International standard EN 197-1: (2011)).</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2019-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time period corresponds to data collection period (2019).</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
